    explanation: 'Overall explanation Key influencer visual is Microsoft\'s attempt to visualize a multiple regression algorithm where multiple variables (number of cars owned, Occupation, Education) affect the customer\'s Yearly income. In multiple regression, we have the equation: Y = a + b1x1 + b2x2 + .... + bnxn Where Y = yearly income; x1 = number of cars owned; x2 = Education, etc. and b1, b2, b3 are their respective coefficients. Since each variable may have a different scale, it makes comparison between them a difficult task. For example, the below two statements, although individually looks fine, they do not make sense when we analyze them together because the number of cars owned and the number of employees reporting to you are on different scales. When the number of cars owned goes up by 2, yearly income goes up by $10K and When the number of employees that report to you goes up by 15, yearly income goes up by $10K. Buying a car is a big event in one\'s life, and you would agree that buying 1 car is not equivalent to 1 additional employee reporting to you. To overcome the scale issue, the visual normalizes the dimensions using their standard deviations. Using standard deviation, the key influencer brings all the input variables on a common scale. So, whenever you see different numeric input variables, you would know that for every increase in 1 standard deviation (of its value), the yearly income increases by Y. Option The standard deviation of the number of cars owned is the correct answer. Reference Link: https://docs.microsoft.com/enus/power-bi/visuals/power-bi-visualization-influencers#interpret-continuous-key-influencers https://www.bluegranite.com/blog/key-influencers-visualization-regression-models-in-power-bi PBIX File Link: https://github.com/ravikiran-srini/PL-300-Exam-PBIX-files-and-Sampledata/blob/main/Case%20Study%20AI%20Rudder.pbix'
